- Support for info in /proc and /sys (sysfs, debugfs) would be nice.
- Read-write FUSE bridge (read-only already exists via briefs-utils).
- Broader test coverage (e.g., xfstests integration, crash-consistency tests)
- Annotate the source code thoroughly once things are more stable
- Move away from any deprecated kernel functions BrieFS may be using. Likely to
  come naturally as it's updated to work with newer kernels, but still needs
  calling out.
- Start honoring mount options.
- Make list of relevant mount options to honor, whether fs independent or
  unique to briefs.
- Make briefs(5) man page.
- support xattrs
- Quotas
- POSIX ACLs
- direct I/O
- add export_operations so BrieFS can be exported via NFS
- online resize (or any resize)
- extent inode map/add inodes to existing volume

Much further down the list, if ever, items:
- Optional data journaling
- reflink/COW, fscrypt, fsverity, casefolding
- build-in compression
